20–Male":"1120–Deceased","1124–Male":"1124–Deceased","1054–1135":"1054–1135","1060–Female":"1060–Deceased","1090":"1090","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","1116":"1116","1159":"1159","5 January 1083":"5 January 1083","1124":"1124","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","after 1135":"after 1135","1208":"1208","1108":"1108","Creyssel,France":"France","Rodez, France":"Rodez, France","Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France","Rodez, Aveyron, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, France","Millau, Aveyron, France":"Millau, Aveyron, France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Hughes","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Hugues Capet  (  ?938–96 ) was ruler of France (  987–96 ) and founder of the Capetian dynasty.  See  <b>Hugh</b> ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"or","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Originally the name of the god of thunder in Norse mythology, Thor (Old Norse <i>Þórr</i>). It was not used as a personal name during the Middle Ages. The modern name is either a late 18th-century revival of the god's name or else a vernacular development of   Tord ."],"variants":[{"name":"Thor","meanings":["Originally the name of the god of thunder in Norse mythology, Thor (Old Norse <i>Þórr</i>). It was not used as a personal name during the Middle Ages. The modern name is either a late 18th-century revival of the god's name or else a vernacular development of   Tord ."]}]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Attainment’."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Rodez","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Roden in High Ercall (Shropshire). The place takes its name from the river Roden, itself probably named in Celtic as ‘swift river, rushing river’ (British <i>Rutunā</i>).","Irish: from <b>Ó Rodáin</b>, see   Redding  .","German: variant of   Rode  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rodine","meanings":["Swedish: variant of <b>Rodén</b> (see   Roden  ).","Americanized form, under French influence, of Russian and Jewish   Rodin  ."]},{"name":"Redding","meanings":["English: habitational name from Reading, the county seat of Berkshire, from Old English <i>Rēadingas</i> ‘people of <i>Rēad(a)</i>’, a byname meaning ‘red’.","Irish: from <b>Ó Rodáin</b> ‘descendant of <i>Rodán</i>’, a personal name derived from a diminutive of <i>rod</i> ‘strong, lively, spirited’. Anglicized forms with other vowels, as in Rudden, Reddan, may be derived from a variant <b>Ó Roidín</b>. Current Anglicized Irish forms usually have a double <i>d</i>.","German: patronymic from any of the ancient Germanic personal names with the first element <i>rād</i> ‘counsel, advice’."]},{"name":"Rodin","meanings":["From Greek: short form of <i>Hērodion</i> ‘devotee of Hera’. The name Herodion was borne by a kinsman of St Paul mentioned in the New Testament (Romans 16:11); according to post-biblical tradition he became bishop of Patras and met a martyr's death."]},{"name":"Rhoden","meanings":["English (West Midlands): variant of   Roden  .","German: variant of   Roden  .","German: habitational name from a place so named (Hesse, Saxony-Anhalt, Silesia)."]},{"name":"Roaden","meanings":["Altered form of Irish or German   Roden  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Comte Hughes I or II de Rodez was born in 1085, in Millau, Aveyron, France, his father, Vicomte Richard IV de Lodeve, Carlat, comte Rodez, was 31 and his mother, Adelais or Adelaide, was 26. He married vicomtesse Emengarde de Creyssls in 1108, in France. They were the parents of at least 5 sons. He died in 1159, in Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1085–1159":"1085–1159","1090–Female":"1090–Surnud","1110–Male":"1110–Surnud","1112–1208":"1112–1208","1116–Male":"1116–Surnud","1120–Male":"1120–Surnud","1124–Male":"1124–Surnud","1054–1135":"1054–1135","1060–Female":"1060–Surnud","1090":"1090","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","1116":"1116","1159":"1159","5 January 1083":"5. jaanuar 1083","1124":"1124","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","after 1135":"pärast 1135","1208":"1208","1108":"1108","Creyssel,France":"Prantsusmaa","Rodez, France":"Rodez, Prantsusmaa","Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, Prantsusmaa","Rodez, Aveyron, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Prantsusmaa","Millau, Aveyron, France":"Millau, Aveyron, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1085–1159":"1085–1159","1090–Female":"1090–Kuollut","1110–Male":"1110–Kuollut","1112–1208":"1112–1208","1116–Male":"1116–Kuollut","1120–Male":"1120–Kuollut","1124–Male":"1124–Kuollut","1054–1135":"1054–1135","1060–Female":"1060–Kuollut","1090":"1090","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","1116":"1116","1159":"1159","5 January 1083":"5. tammikuuta 1083","1124":"1124","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","after 1135":"1135 jälkeen","1208":"1208","1108":"1108","Creyssel,France":"Ranska","Rodez, France":"Rodez, Ranska","Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, Ranska","Rodez, Aveyron, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Ranska","Millau, Aveyron, France":"Millau, Aveyron, Ranska"},"fr":{"1085–1159":"1085–1159","1090–Female":"1090–Décédée","1110–Male":"1110–Décédé","1112–1208":"1112–1208","1116–Male":"1116–Décédé","1120–Male":"1120–Décédé","1124–Male":"1124–Décédé","1054–1135":"1054–1135","1060–Female":"1060–Décédée","1090":"1090","1110":"1110","1120":"1120","1054":"1054","1085":"1085","1060":"1060","1116":"1116","1159":"1159","5 January 1083":"5 janvier 1083","1124":"1124","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","after 1